	"description": "The Fermat test is based on a result from number theory known as Fermat’s little\ntheorem.\n\nAccording to Fermat’s little theorem, if n is a prime number and d is any\npositive integer less than n, then d raised to the nth power is congruent to d \nmodulo n.\n\nIf two numbers have the same remainder when divided by n then they are said to\nbe congruent modulo n. d modulo n is simply the remainder of a number d when\ndivided by n.\n\nFor example, 34 is congruent to 16 (modulo 3) as \n34 modulo 3 &#x3D; 1 and 16 ",
